HEADWORD: Osseous
<hw>Os"se*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>osseus</ets>, from <ets>os</ets>, <ets>ossis</ets> bone; akin to
Gr. <grk>'oste`on</grk>, Skr. <ets>asthi</ets>. Cf.
<er>Oyster</er>.]</ety> <def>Composed of bone; resembling bone; capable
of forming bone; bony; ossific.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

